      .wrapper-small
        h4.align-center
          strong A Full-Scale Prototype
        h6.alttitle.align-center for the most popular and downloaded weather app of all time.
        .column-section.clearfix
            p The Weather Channel asked Makeable to redesign their flagship app. During the process, I prototyped a concept to present to Apple. The design featured animated backgrounds that changed according to the weather. It also has a customizable card system that the user can adjust to match their lifestyle. The flagship feature of the concept is WeatherLens, which crowdsourced information about the&nbsp;weather.
      .wrapper.xtra-wide
        .spacer.spacer-big
        .wolf-grid.clearfix(data-mouseparallax='true' data-randomhorizontaloffset='true')
          .wolf-item
            .wolf-item-inner
              p When severe weather strikes, the background illustration and dominant color would change. There also are no ads, and the app pulls in relevant social updates from Instagram and Twitter.
          .wolf-item
            .wolf-item-inner
              .wolf-media.portfolio-media(style='background:url(../img/twc/hurricane.gif) repeat-x; background-size: auto 100%; background-position: 50% 50%;background-position:fixed;')
                  img(data-aload='../img/twc/twc_02-medium.png' srcset="../img/twc/twc_02-small.png 640w, ../img/twc/twc_02-medium.png 1480w, ../img/twc/twc_02-large.png 1600w" alt='Weather Channel Severe Weather Screen')
